To avoid systematical errors, which could be
produced due to any possible detection losses under
high loads of spectrometer, it was checked out by the
method of two source.  The ultimate load of the
spectrometer was limited so as not to exceed 5% in all
of the measurements.
Second Ge-Li detector, which has been used, has low
background with ultimate sensitivity ~50-100 decay in
hour. The spectrometer was used to measure
gamma-spectra samples and monitor foils 1.5 year after
the samples were irradiated.
